ask\\\"}],\\n    \\\"postToolUse\\\": [\\n      {\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks cursor post-task\\\", \\\"matcher\\\": \\\"Task\\\"},\\n      {\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks cursor post-todo\\\", \\\"matcher\\\": \\\"TodoWrite\\\"}\\n    ]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n**After:**\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"hooks\\\": {\\n    \\\"subagentStart\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks cursor subagent-start\\\"}],\\n    \\\"subagentStop\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks cursor subagent-stop\\\"}],\\n    \\\"postToolUse\\\": [{\\\"command\\\": \\\"entire hooks cursor post-todo\\\", \\\"matcher\\\": \\\"TodoWrite\\\"}]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n### Data Model Differences Discovered\\n\\nThe dedicated `subagentStart/subagentStop` hooks have a **different data model** than the tool-based approach:\\n\\n| Field | Tool Hooks (`preToolUse[Task]`) | Dedicated Hooks (`subagentStart`) |\\n|-------|--------------------------------|----------------------------------|\\n| Task ID | `tool_use_id` | Not provided |\\n| Task type | Extract from `tool_input` | `subagent_type` field |\\n| Task prompt | Extract from `tool_input` | `prompt` field |\\n| Transcript | Build from `SubagentID` | `agent_transcript_path` |\\n| Status | Implicit | `status` field (\\\"completed\\\"/\\\"error\\\") |\\n\\n**Trade-off:** The dedicated hooks are more semantic but don't provide `tool_use_id`, which the current framework uses for pre/post task state correlation. This may need downstream changes in `lifecycle.go` if task state tracking relies on that ID.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":8,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":313,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":126246,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":313},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYHeRJ7mExHaySimLYtJ5\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"7ab778e8-171e-4ef2-92a4-5d2daec90d12\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-